A swamp snake is a monster found in the Temple Trekking minigame. When it reaches 0 hitpoints, it should turn into a dead swamp snake.

Dead snakes can be skinned by using a knife on the snake corpse to obtain swamp snake hides. The hides can be tanned into snakeskin and made into armour. The swamp snake hide looks different from normal snake hide, although the snakeskin and armour crafted from it will be no different.

It is possible to safespot them in medium and hard treks by attacking them before the timer and then hiding behind the vegetation in the bottom left corner.

Drops[edit | edit source]

Item Quantity Rarity Price High Alch
Snake hide (swamp)2–5Always[d 1]518–1,29542–105
Bones1Always[d 2]770
  1. ^ Requires knife to skin the dead snake.
  2. ^ Only when damaged by the trekking partner after killing it initially, which replaces the snake hide drop.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • A glitch can occur where it reaches 0 hitpoints but then is given the max health of 1 and restored. It then may be attacked by your trekking partner who deals a finishing blow, which makes it die without turning into a dead swamp snake and just produces bones as a drop.

A '''swamp snake''' is a [[Monsters|monster]] found in the [[Temple Trekking]] [[Minigames|minigame]]. When it reaches 0 [[hitpoints]], it should turn into a dead swamp snake.

Dead snakes can be skinned by using a [[knife]] on the snake corpse to obtain [[snake hide (swamp)|swamp snake hide]]s. The hides can be tanned into [[snakeskin]] and made into armour. The swamp snake hide looks different from normal snake hide, although the snakeskin and [[snakeskin armour|armour]] crafted from it will be no different.

It is possible to [[safespot]] them in medium and hard treks by attacking them before the timer and then hiding behind the vegetation in the bottom left corner.
